<h2 id="tldr">Tl;DR</h2>

<p>Our goal when solving a system of equations is to create an upper-triangular matrix through elimination</p>

\[a_{11}x_1 + a_{12}x_2 + \dots + a_{1n}x_n = \alpha \\
0 + a_{22}x_2 + \dots + a_{2n} x_n = \beta\\
\dots+a_{nn} = \gamma\]

<p>Once we have done so, we can then use back substituition in order to solve for each individual unknown.</p>

